node.text:
I think this year challenged everyone. In every way shape, or form. I think many of us wished 2020 looked differently.

It’s easy to look at the things that should have been, could have been & didn’t happen and let bitterness settle in, but I’m a firm believer that struggling is where we blossom and to not let our hearts grow cold in the storms.

So as I look back through my camera roll, there was so much smiling, new adventures and joy given the confines & chaos of 2020. Thank you @rachelveltriphoto for many of these memories engrained in my heart.

I’m going embrace the disappointments of 2020 while also celebrating the moments of joy entering into 2021. 

My theme for 2021 is to be “All In”, In everything I do and not hold back out of fear. To be more decisive and confident in myself, especially as a business woman.

@twenty2nutrition GIVEAWAY!!! 

What is your theme moving into 2021? 

To enter into our winter box giveaway launching tonight at 7pm EST like the post & tag a friend below and tell them something they did this year that was incredible along with your new theme moving into 2021!

node.text:
We go through phases and seasons of motivation.

Right now, my motivation has taken a hiatus. Getting back into training with everything going on, has been tough. Working out for the first time in my life, just isn’t a priority for me right now and that’s ok. I’ll swallow that tough pill.

I didn’t want to do this workout, but I knew my mental health needed it. Josh told me to go workout, he would pack packages.

So I turned off my brain, grabbed some dumbbells and went outside to workout in some sunshine.

It was exactly what I needed. To push myself until my lungs hurt. To break a sweat and to demolish the stress I was keeping inside.

You’re not going to always have motivation but what you can always have is the choice to do something you know that’s right for you even though you don’t want to. This is how discipline & consistency bloom.

Workout: sorry for the crappy filming, I didn’t intend on filming or posting this. 🙏🏼

10 reps of every exercise.

I broke it down into 2 circuits. Then finished with 4 minutes of ab core work on the ground. 3 rounds each circuit. 1 minute rest between circuits.

Happy Monday. I want to know what you do when your motivation takes a hike. This can be anything, not just fitness 🙌🏽

#10weekspostpartum

node.title: No one is motivated 100% of the time.

node.text:
Especially in front of almost 1 million of you...

But it’s time to start normalizing postpartum depression and all it’s faucets of how it effect mothers, so they can stop struggling in silence and feel comfortable to speak up and get the help they need.

I shared my Postpartum struggles on my story a week or so ago because I’ve always been honest about my journey and this is no different, so why hide it?

 I had thousands & thousands of responses back of women in similar situations. Women who felt hopeless and alone or that something was wrong with them because everyone else appeared “happy” on IG or those around them.

I avoided posting it here because honestly the fear of people being cruel or saying it’s for “seeking attention” and all the other accusations & stigmas that cause women to stay silent during postpartum because I didn’t think I could mentally handle it.

Fuck that.

We do not need to be ashamed of our emotions. We do not need to be ashamed of where we are, we do not need to be ashamed of the struggles we are going through and we do NOT need to hide these feelings and be afraid to ask for help because of the stigma surrounding our struggles or the lack of understanding/education from others 👏🏼👏🏼

On my story is @drcassidy who specializes in PPD who was kind enough to talk about depression and how it can manifest & effect mothers differently. It will permanently be saved in my highlights to refer to or send to someone in need. There’s also many other accounts saved who are helpful too.

Mamas, You are not alone. You are worthy and you are so strong. There is no shame in getting help or opening up about how you feel. Your emotions are valid and real.♥️

Feel free to talk about your struggles below. It’s freeing 🙌🏽This is a safe place and I will delete all negativity.

node.text:
A video of Jaden and myself getting adjusted☺️
.
.

Our entire family has been seeing @drmarcov since I was early pregnancy with Jaden. Without him, I wouldn’t have been able to stay active my first pregnancy due to SPD! He significantly helped make the spd pain manageable for me along with reducing back/hip pain. Jaden enjoys it too ☺️

Benefits for pregnancy:
👉🏻Find a REPUTABLE Chiropractor that specializes in Webster Technique. 

👉🏻 Webster Technique can help keep the pelvis balanced which can encourage baby to get in optimal position. The round ligaments take a beating during pregnancy and this technique can help keep them “happy” as I like to call it.

👉🏻 Reduces low back pain, sciatica relief, pelvic girdle pain and many other nagging aches & pains that can come with pregnancy.

👉🏻 Can help with indigestion
And so much more.

Not all chiropractors are created equal just like any profession. We’ve been seeing @drmarcov for over 3 years for a reason and will continue to. Baby will also be “adjusted” once born just like Jaden was when he was a newborn. Can help with breastfeeding too. Birth can be pretty traumatic on their little necks.

Chiropractic care isn’t for everyone, it definitely isn’t something that’s truly needed but it can make a world of a difference for many. I just wanted to share the things I’ve done during my pregnancy that have significantly helped me and give you tools to make decisions best for you🙏🏼
.
.
Did you see a chiropractor during your pregnancy and did it help you?☺️

node.text:
Of tearing & injury!

TAG A MAMA or friend ♥️ I’ll answer as many questions as I can.

There truly isn’t enough talk/eduction around pelvic floor and core health and it’s a shame because it is so important in women’s health.

The pelvic floor plays a vital role in pelvis stability, pregnancy/birth and postpartum journeys (why you guys see me harp on proper core engagement & breathing properly, pregnant or not)

My dear friend Kelley from @the.revelle and I have a small chit chat and scrape the surface about pelvic floor health & preparing the PF for delivery!🙌🏽

A few misconceptions we wanted to address based off what I asked on my stories!
 
👉🏻Kegels are NOT the “holy grail” exercise to strengthen your pelvic floor before/during pregnancy & postpartum.

👉🏻 In fact doing just kegels can worsen symptoms of incontinence, painful sex & prolapse because it creates overly tight pelvic floor muscles & they are often done WRONG.

👉🏻Kegels are not the “stopping of urine.” Please don’t do this to train your PF as it just focuses on the muscles surrounding the urinary sphincter & can create dysfunction. A correct Kegel is engaging the entire PF bed.

👉🏻 A strong balanced pelvic floor has the ability to engage & LENGTHEN with the same intensity.

👉🏻Preventative care is always the goal and can save you a lot of heart ache. The sooner you can create functionality in your core unit the better. This applies to ALL women (and men) but it Is NEVER to late to heal and restore your core.♥️

My core guide teaches in depth about core health, breathing and core engagement. Link in the bio.

I will always recommend seeing a reputable pelvic floor physio as routine checkups. It’s your health. It can make a world of a difference in your journeys where you are.🙌🏽

You can reach out to @the.revelle or go online to https://pelvicguru.com or https://aptaapps.apta.org//APTAPTDirectory/FindAPTDirectory.aspx to find someone in your area.

Prepping for vaginal delivery:
1. Perineal massage using hands & also the @kegelreleasecurve & epino are devices I’ll be using to help assist with that.
2. Lengthening the pelvic floor along with stretches shown in video!

node.title: Kegel MYTHS| Pelvic floor health & preparing for birth to reduce chances

Three years of being able to call you “hubby” and three glorious years of choosing you day in and day out 🖤 @jhalliday14 

*** ending got cut off 😫 I’ll share the rest on my story!

I watch our wedding video often. Every-time I get super emotional, even when I watch it solely because I’m super mad at you and by the end of it I’m no longer mad 😂

I love you. Thank you for being you and thank you for being the man our family needs. 3 years strong and so many more to go. 🙌🏽

Will be posting some more wedding stuff on the stories.🥰🥺
.
.

node.text:
A little over a year and a half ago we launched @twenty2nutrition in our home. Over the past year, we moved and were blessed to pack out of our garage and now here we are moving into our first warehouse! Feeling so unbelievably thankful.🙏🏼

Josh and I have poured our heart and soul into Twenty2 building it from the ground up. A two man team, with a lot of other obligations to manage on top of it.

Josh put in so many 80 hour weeks working full time at his other intensive job while also getting what needed to be done for Twenty2. A lot of 4am mornings and long long nights.

I learned to manage being a full time stay at home mom, run Twenty2 and manage all things business for “hannahbower2.”

We have finally reached a place where we can stop pumping the break and dive full force into our company and that feels so unbelievably good.😭🙌🏽

We couldn’t have done it without your belief and support in us, so thank you. We may not be the largest company out there, but we pack every order with love and truly care and are so proud of Twenty2 and what we stand for.

We are truly excited to see what the next year has in store for Twenty2. We have so many exciting things in the works for you guys🙌🏽

To honor and thank you guys! We’re giving away 3 $100 gift cards to @twenty2nutrition!

To ENTER:
1. Follow me & @twenty2nutrition 
2. Comment something positive or your favorite Twenty2 product to a friend!
Dattsssss it! 🥰

node.text:
Getting baby in optimal position! 🙌🏽- TAG a mama!

As you guys know this lil baby was breech at my 32 week ultra sound. Seems this baby and Jaden are already bonding. 😂 Yesterday, I was able to see my massage body worker and we successfully were able to turn baby to head down 🙏🏼

Today, I saw my wonderful doula to reiterate and encourage baby’s head down position and this is what we did and my “homework” everyday until birth. I thought I would share all of what I’ve done♥️

All of these positions help open the pelvis and the shifting from side to side can help baby get in the best position for birth which is LOA. ( left occiput anterior)- check out spinning babies for more info. 😊

Side lying release- really important you are straight. You will need someone to assist you.

In addition to these I also have been doing: ( posted in flipping baby highlight)
1. Pelvic floor work- perineal massage. Prone to a hypertonic PF.- super important for birth.
2. Stability work in my pelvis as I’m also prone to instability.
3. 💥Inversions- both handstand style and lying down coupled with side lying release, rebozo & massage. ( not shown- this was huge yesterday in flipping this angel)
4. Fascia & massage work
5. Ball swivels

If you’re in the Denver area would 100% recommend both of these ladies.🖤
* My Doula- Donna Rigert 
* Harmony’s Family Cooperative- Regina

node.text:
I literally was going from one exercise to the next before this and not feeling motivated...at all. Had no intentions of filming my workout tonight. But here we are! LIVE workout to follow along. Grab some music. Let’s do this.

Typically when I feel this way I know I need to spike my heart rate to get some happy endorphins going. So I tend to do mini MIIT ( medium intensity interval training) because I wouldn’t necessarily call this hiiit buttttt the feeling after is worttthhhhh it. 👏🏼.
.

Broke a sweat, got some happy feelings and got SOMETHING IN.

A bad workout is better than no workout. Any movement is better than nothing ♥️ You can add weight, resistance and maybe so more plyos to the reverse lunges to make it HIIT!

Workout: 10 minutes
20 gate swings
20 reverse lunges- half way through I switched to forward lunges
10-12 pikes peak push-up
REST 10-20seconds

Modify the pikes peak pushups if you are coning or don’t have proper form. Just go on knees!

#20weekspregnant

node.title: The workout you do when you don’t want to workout! 😂🙏🏼

node.text:
Let’s gooooooo, FAM! #sweatisgold. All you need is yourself and a little extra push to get out and move your body. Turn off your brain and go.🙌🏽
.
.
It’s absolutely ok to lack or have ZERO motivation during this time. It’s ok to gain weight or even lose strength. You have all the time to get back after it when this is all over. 🖤 please, don’t be too hard on yourself. Extend yourself grace. This is a really weird time. “Muscle memory” truly is a thing and your progress will not be completely lost or lost at all.🙏🏼
.
.
You also don’t need equipment or a home gym to keep healthy. Your body itself and nature is your own gym! 🙌🏽
.
.
For this workout I ran .75 mile. Stopped, did about 15 minutes of the following exercises than ran back.

No reps or sets. Go until you can’t any longer on an exercise and switch immediately to something else!

Just get your body moving. Endorphins flowing. You’ll feel better.

We also go to see baby today! Looks just like Jaden 🥺 #13weekspregnant

It’s HEREEEEE. 😍 My collection with @ptulaactive launches this Sunday, August 1st. 6pm EST.

Support code is Hannah. It’s no different than any other launch 🙏🏼

🥵 I. can. not. believe this project collab is finally here. I’m beyond honored and I can’t tell you how much your excitement about the pieces the past couple days makes me even more excited. 😭🙌🏽

We love a good neutral but sometimes you just need a little spice of color in the closet. 🙏🏼

Head to my stories for all the details! I’ll have a saved highlight for more info on each piece. As the week goes I’ll add more to it! There’s already so much on there.

Which color or piece is your favorite 😍

node.text:
Happy freaking Sunday! 🙌🏽 Full Body Circuit for the win! Workout below.

Quick announcement for those interested!

@twenty2nutrition second largest SALE of the year is today! 4:45pm EST ♥️- 40% off apparel. By one protein get another full price product 25% off. Plus restocking of joint pill + fall flavors.

A few ppl who comment & like this post will win @twenty2nutrition or a gift card for themselves or to give to someone else to try!

These weekly full body challenges go up on the app weekly. 🙌🏽 link in the bio.

Workout Challenge: 5 rounds little rest!
Reps in the videos

💧 Lunge jumps to lunge walks
💧Kneeling snatch: this is a great way to learn to begin to sit your hips back in movement with more control. Kneeling also makes it a great core exercise with the single arm movement.
💧 90/90 Swivels to squat- I like this for mobility work incorporated into the workout 
💧Runners bicep curls- as fast as you can with as heavy as weight as you can go🔥 
💧single leg + both leg box jumps. Modify and just do regular if need be.
💧 Side planks to bear plank hovers- keep inner core engaged to manage the pressure within your abdomen. If you see coning or breadloafing, modify to knees 🙏🏼

Okay that was a lot! 😵‍💫 I apologize. Hope you guys are having an amazing day. Outfit is my collection with @ptulaactive launching aug 1st!!

node.text:
In order for something to become a habit, you have to keep doing it even through the times you don’t feel like it. Discipline is created through being consistent.

We all know motivation isn’t a constant continuous thing you just have.

It comes and goes. 

These are a few tips I like to do when motivation is less than par.

Comment below your tips of staying consistent. 🙏🏼

1. I’ve said this for years. Turn off your brain. Get up. Put your shoes on. Grab your keys & just go. Don’t think. Just go. Making that decision is the hardest step but you’ll be so thankful afterwards.
2. Change up your workouts to something you really enjoy. I tend to go back to “playing” and do gymnastics type conditioning because it brings me joy.
3. Wear an outfit that makes me feel confident.
4. Get out to the “all or nothing” mindset. 5 min is always better than nothing and contributes to creating discipline. 
5. Evaluate your why! This one is important. If it’s solely based on how you look, creating consistency and a lifestyle is really difficult and often leads to  disappointment or yo yo dieting.

Just remember to keep chipping away because through this process, motivation will be sparked again ♥️

NOTE: Some of these moves I did are extremely advanced. Please don’t try them unless you know your abilities and or have a history of some of these movements 🙏🏼

node.text:
We have a walker Y’all. 🙌🏽 Siah took his first steps of course when @jhalliday14 was gone 🤣

This kiddo may have had a rough go in the beginning but it hasn’t stopped him from trying to keep up with big brother. 😭 #9monthsold #babiesfirststeps

Full body madness. A last minute workout but mannnn too good to not share. 🙌🏽🔥 Walked out on cloud 9 which is literally the best feeling.

This will be on the app in a LIVE format so you can follow along or go at your own pace.

Look, I’m a full lover of accessory fun workouts that are unique. They can be fun, motivating and keep you consistent…but they are accessory for a reason. You will never go wrong doing the basics and repeating them OFTEN. May be more boring…but they work & are tried and true to be effective🙏🏼

This is a 3-5 round circuit. The heavier weight you use, will require more rest after the round. If you are using lighter weights, try to keep a steady pace through all rounds.

Workout:
 💧 5-6 sumo dead’s: modify and use dumbbells
💦5-6 Pull-ups: modify and use assistance or standing pull up rows.
💧10 SRDL- modify Put other foot down for assistance
💦10 Bodyweight Extensions: use resistance band to assist you
💧 10 Push-up to plate slides: modify and go on a bench or knees— posted on story because I forgot. 🥴
💦12 or AMRAP Deadbugs: I’m using my hand as feedback to see if I’m regulating pressure. I still have some healing in my DR although it’s functional! Modify: limit range of motion or do deadbug hold or marches!

Also, don’t allow workouts that intimidate you keep you from trying or modifying them. We all start from somewhere! This workout can be modified for all levels 🙏🏼

node.text:
9 months in vs 9 months out 😭♥️

An appreciation post for this body of mine and what it has provided for Josiah from nourishing him in my womb to nourishing him earth side, despite all the obstacles thrown our way.🙏🏼

I was crippled with stress, worry and anxiety around breastfeeding. Siah refused both a bottle and a paci, had a tongue and lip tie revision and then all the formulas out there contained one or a couple of his food triggers.

It was not as simple as “just switch to formula already. This is old” like so many would tell me.

When I went through the elimination diet, I was down to about 10 foods I was eating for weeks. If I slipped up on accident, I’d feel immense guilt because I knew the pain it would cause him.  I then would panic about what would happen if I lost my milk supply. How would I feed him? What formula would work? What bottle would he finally take? 

I got some of the nastiest and hurtful messages this postpartum. It was honestly really hard at times.

In a sense, I don’t fault the judgement. I post my life online. It comes with the territory. I myself, never understood the hardships of breastfeeding through allergies until, I was that mom with her baby.

But as a mom, you know what’s best for your kiddo & yourself. Breastfeeding was honestly the less stressed scenario for me. It was also what I wanted to do. Period.

And now here we are, over the mountain and still breastfeeding strong 😭I could cry happy tears of relief and joy even if it’s still hard at times as Siah is still waking 4-8x a night.🥴 #justaseason

But we ARE sleeping better than before and life IS easier. We have made it over the  biggest hump.

So if you’re struggling, or on a similar journey I was on & so many others…just know it does get easier and you are not alone. Listen to your mama instincts and don’t let the noise and judgement of others keep you from doing what’s best for you & your family. However that looks ♥️

P.S Please please, know this is not to make any one feel bad or guilty for not continuing breastfeeding. This was what I chose and what I felt was the best for myself and Siah🙏🏼 I absolutely know formula is best for some families too!

node.text:
Happy Friday! Some of my favorite exercises that target the adductors. 🙌🏽

This is a weak area for me and an area I’ve really had to strengthen to help imbalances in my pelvis. Especially before  and during my pregnancies. Made a world of a difference in my second pregnancy in minimizing pelvic girdle pain.

The glute bridge with adduction squeeze is a great alternative if you don’t have an adductor machine. It’s also just a great overall core exercise. Squeeze as hard as you can for 5x then hold while squeezing a ball or block as hard as you can for 5-10 seconds. Repeat 5x

I always try to add in adductor work into leg days. Working all muscle groups in your training is important to avoid muscle imbalances 🙏🏼

What’s your fav adductor exercise!?

node.text:
This past weekend we had our very first baby sitter and night out the town 😭🙌🏽

If you watched my stories, I expressed the array of emotions I was experiencing. Doubt, worry, anxiety & hope as many of you know this postpartum journey has not been all that easy.🙏🏼

Did Siah wake up as I expected? Yup.
Did the baby sister have a hard time getting him back down? Indeed.
Did he take the milk I pumped? Not really.

So many of my worries did indeed happen….BUT!!

Siah did eventually fall asleep and stayed asleep until we got home. 🙏🏼
The baby sitter loved it and was absolutely incredible.
And the icing on the cake, I got quality time with my husband and dear friends and my worries of having a baby sitter has drastically gone down. 😭

Mommying/parenting is hard. The guilt of stepping away & getting in quality time with my husband @jhalliday14 has been a challenging journey for me this postpartum. But taking care of yourself & your marriage is also so so important.

Kids change the dynamics of your relationship, so it requires a little more tender care to make sure the spark stays aflame ♥️

How do you make sure your relationship is being nourished? Did you find your relationship changed after kiddos?

node.text:
My entire world ♥️

I got the chance to take my littles to my favorite childhood place growing up, waterworld! Some of my fondest memories are from waterworld and to get to recreate these memories for my kiddos brings me so much joy. 

Like I got giddy inside taking Jaden through the exact same routine my parents did with me and to see his face light up was everything 😭

There was a time when I was so afraid to be a mother and how my life would look, and now I cannot see my life any other way. 🙏🏼

Happy Friday. 🙌🏽 any fun plans for the fourth!!?

node.text:
A Spicy back day 🙌🏽 Majority of the time I prefer doing a little bit of upper body with a focus on 1 or 2 muscles, but sometimes a solid back day is everything.

One of the keys to a successful back day is learning how to retract the shoulder blades before pulling. This allows for optimal pulling mechanics and targeting the correct muscles.

As always, a few form yup suggestions! 🙏🏼

Also, the Prone Ys can be deceivingly tough. If you can do it with weight use your body weight or bands!

Lastly, I know so many of you hate pull-ups: any form of them. I get it, they can really suck. 😩🥴 but they are a game changer for pulling movements and gaining strength. If you can’t do one, I’ll post another tutorial here soon! Even assisted or pull-up rows at an incline are awesome.

Happy Thursday! Tell me something good that’s happened today 🥰

node.text:
Bis & Tris! 🙌🏽 I don’t really strive for massive pumps, but sometimes when the pump hits you’re like damnnn, “I feel good” (in a James Brown voice) 😂

Anywho, happy freaking Monday.  If you plan an upper body workout, this one is solid. I promise.🙏🏼

Workout:

•Bicep Curls ( with hammer eccentric): because these are low reps challenge yourself. This is a strength set. Important to rest a MINimum of 90sec to 3 minutes between sets. Not every workout has to be “go go go”

•Wall Triceps Extensions: 8 reps each way. Make sure to keep elbows pinned straight forward & extend the weight as far as it will go.

•Seated curls SS lateral triceps extensions. Keep elbows fixed in place as you curl & extend.

•Cable 1 1/2 curls SS overhead extensions: important you don’t arch your back & flare your ribs as you extend. Keep ribs tucked, neutral pelvis.

•90 Iso Holds: these are brutal at the end of the workout 🔥 🥵 so use assistance if you need! To make it more full body, squeeze all your muscles at “tight” as they can.

This went up on the app last week along with a few others ♥️
